# Plugin Development Conventions

This monorepo hosts Cursor plugins under `plugins/`. Each plugin is a self-contained package.

## Creating or Modifying Plugins

Use `/zoto-create-plugin` to scaffold a new plugin. For modifications to existing plugins, follow these conventions.

## Required Structure

Every plugin must have:
- `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json` — manifest with `name`, `displayName`, `version`, `description`, `author`, `license`
- Entry in `.cursor-plugin/marketplace.json` at the repo root
- `README.md` (>50 lines), `LICENSE`, `CHANGELOG.md`

## Component Frontmatter

| Component | File pattern | Required frontmatter |
|-----------|-------------|---------------------|
| Agent | `agents/*.md` | `name`, `description` |
| Skill | `skills/*/SKILL.md` | `name`, `description` |
| Command | `commands/*.md` | `name`, `description` |
| Rule | `rules/*.mdc` | `description` |

## Skill Requirements

- Skill directory name must match `name` in frontmatter
- Each skill must have `evals/evals.json` with >= 2 test cases and assertions
- Keep `SKILL.md` under 500 lines

## Naming

- Plugin names: lowercase kebab-case (`zoto-<domain>`)
- All identifiers: kebab-case, no leading/trailing hyphens, no consecutive hyphens

## Validation

Before submitting changes, run:
1. `node scripts/validate-template.mjs`
2. `node scripts/validate-skills.mjs`
3. `pnpm test`
